#. <section class="sutta" id="sn2.5"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn2.5:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 2"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 2"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn2.5:0.2"
msgid "1. Paṭhamavagga"
msgstr "1. The First Chapter"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn2.5:0.3"
msgid "5. Dāmalisutta"
msgstr "5. With Dāmali"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn2.5:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn2.5:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho dāmali devaputto abhikkantāya rattiyā abhikkantavaṇṇo kevalakappaṃ "
"jetavanaṃ obhāsetvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ "
"abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi."
msgstr ""
"Then, late at night, the glorious god Dāmali, lighting up the entire Jeta’s "
"Grove, went up to the Buddha, bowed, stood to one side,"

msgctxt "sn2.5:1.3"
msgid ""
"Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho dāmali devaputto bhagavato santike imaṃ gāthaṃ abhāsi:"
msgstr "and recited this verse in the Buddha’s presence:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="pts2ed" id="pts2ed1.108"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn2.5:2.1"
msgid "“Karaṇīyametaṃ brāhmaṇena,"
msgstr "“This is what should be done by a brahmin:"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.5:2.2"
msgid "Padhānaṃ akilāsunā;"
msgstr "unrelenting striving."

# BB has sensual desires here, but kama in plural normally stands for “sensual pleasures”.
#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.5:2.3"
msgid "Kāmānaṃ vippahānena,"
msgstr "Then, with the giving up of sensual pleasures,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.5:2.4"
msgid "Na tenāsīsate bhavan”ti."
msgstr "they won’t hope to be reborn.”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts1ed" id="pts1ed1.48"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn2.5:3.1"
msgid "“Natthi kiccaṃ brāhmaṇassa, (dāmalīti bhagavā)"
msgstr "“The brahmin has nothing left to do,” said the Buddha to Dāmali,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.5:3.2"
msgid "Katakicco hi brāhmaṇo;"
msgstr "“for they’ve completed the task."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.5:3.3"
msgid "Yāva na gādhaṃ labhati nadīsu,"
msgstr "So long as a person fails to gain a footing in the river,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.5:3.4"
msgid "Āyūhati sabbagattebhi jantu;"
msgstr "they strive with every limb."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.5:3.5"
msgid "Gādhañca laddhāna thale ṭhito yo,"
msgstr "But someone who has gained a footing and stands on dry land"

#. <br>
#. VAR: sova → soti (bj, pts1-2, mr) | hoti (s1-3, km) | so (?)
msgctxt "sn2.5:3.6"
msgid "Nāyūhatī pāragato hi sova."
msgstr "need not strive, for they have reached the far shore."

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn2.5:4.1"
msgid "Esūpamā dāmali brāhmaṇassa,"
msgstr "Dāmali, this is a simile for the brahmin,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.5:4.2"
msgid "Khīṇāsavassa nipakassa jhāyino;"
msgstr "with defilements ended, self-disciplined, and practicing absorption."

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.5:4.3"
msgid "Pappuyya jātimaraṇassa antaṃ,"
msgstr "Since they’ve reached the end of rebirth and death,"

#. <br>
#. VAR: hi so”ti → hotīti (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn2.5:4.4"
msgid "Nāyūhatī pāragato hi so”ti."
msgstr "they need not strive, for they have reached the far shore.”"
